Daily Report

09 October, 2021

This report is updated automatically each day to highlight key insights from the MosquitoAlertBCN platform. It focuses on the 7-day-ahead forecast of the Vector Risk Index (VRI) for tiger mosquitoes (Aedes albopictus) in Barcelona. This provides a relative measure of the variation in the risk of human contact with tiger mosquitoes across Barcelona and over time. The 7-day-ahead forecast (which starts on the current day) is based on the weather forecast provided daily by the Meteorological Service of Catalonia. The VRI forecast is updated between 11:30 am and 12:30 pm each day.

City-Wide Trends

During the next 7 days, we estimate the mean VRI in Barcelona will be 0.1 and the maximum will be 0.27, occuring on October 09. Figure 1 shows the mean and maximum values estimated for each day, starting 30-days ago and extending 7-days ahead of today.

Figure 1: Estimated city-wide VRI during past 30 days and coming 7 days. Red line indicates maximum values each day; blue indicates means. Vertical black dotted line shows current day.

District VRI

Figure 2 shows mean VRI estimates for each of Barcelona's districts. The district with the highest estimated mean VRI is Gràcia, with a value of 0.14. The means, however, mask a great deal of spatial variation within districts. Figure 3 shows the distribution of VRI estimates for the next 7 days (pooled), made at 20m resolution for each of Barcelona's districts. Districts are ordered according to their median VRI and the city-wide median is shown with the vertical red line.
